01:07.519 --> 01:08.919
Come on.

01:12.974 --> 01:15.926
Come on, Bobby!

01:15.977 --> 01:17.428
Let's go.

01:18.763 --> 01:20.931
Let me stay with you.

01:20.982 --> 01:22.400
Oh, don't cry, sweetheart.

01:22.451 --> 01:23.617
Come on, please?

01:23.702 --> 01:25.870
I don't want
to do this again.

01:26.938 --> 01:32.159
I know, and I'm
so, so, so sorry.

01:32.244 --> 01:34.328
Everything's gonna be ok.

01:35.964 --> 01:37.631
It's ok.

01:41.636 --> 01:43.220
Go on.

02:00.822 --> 02:02.806
What are you doing here?

02:06.912 --> 02:09.747
Thank you.

02:09.814 --> 02:12.500
I am really sorry.
I had to take that.

02:12.584 --> 02:13.984
It's ok.

02:15.370 --> 02:17.654
Fruit plate, huh?

02:17.706 --> 02:20.218
Whatever happened to
the usual bacon and eggs,

02:20.243 --> 02:21.783
extra grease on the side?

02:22.094 --> 02:24.044
Well, I've changed.

02:25.497 --> 02:27.965
Ok, the cantaloupe
is for your benefit.

02:28.016 --> 02:30.196
When we were married,
you were always warning me

02:30.221 --> 02:31.786
about clogged arteries.

02:31.937 --> 02:34.138
And you would always
say to me...

02:34.189 --> 02:37.674
Nobody lives forever.

02:37.726 --> 02:38.859
So how's San Francisco?

02:38.944 --> 02:40.311
Well, you know.

02:40.362 --> 02:42.480
Fog, cable cars,
the usual.

02:42.531 --> 02:44.865
You know, I'm really glad
you called me.

02:44.950 --> 02:46.867
It would be nice
if we saw each other

02:46.952 --> 02:49.737
more than once
every 3 or 4 years.

02:50.872 --> 02:52.990
Maybe we can.

02:56.378 --> 02:58.329
So, give me the updates.

02:58.380 --> 03:00.164
Anybody serious
in your life?

03:00.215 --> 03:02.331
Well, there are all those 
serial killers.

03:02.356 --> 03:03.556
They're pretty serious.

03:03.919 --> 03:05.586
I meant
in your personal life.

03:05.670 --> 03:08.372
No, there isn't.

03:09.874 --> 03:10.975
How about you?

03:11.042 --> 03:13.060
Mm-mmm.

03:15.680 --> 03:18.432
You know, David...

03:19.684 --> 03:21.152
I've been wanting--

03:25.273 --> 03:26.407
Damn it, I--

03:26.491 --> 03:27.825
You gotta go.

03:27.892 --> 03:29.660
I know.

03:29.727 --> 03:31.779
It's ok.
It's comforting to know

03:31.863 --> 03:34.031
that some things
never change.

03:34.082 --> 03:36.167
Look, how much longer
are you gonna be in town?

03:36.234 --> 03:38.619
About a week or so,
probably.

03:38.703 --> 03:40.421
Why don't you come over
to my place for dinner

03:40.505 --> 03:42.039
before you head back?

03:42.090 --> 03:45.176
I still make
a monster cioppino.

03:46.595 --> 03:49.046
I would like that
very much.

03:49.097 --> 03:50.598
Great.

03:54.436 --> 03:56.353
Ciao.
Ciao.

04:00.692 --> 04:02.276
Hey, I'm sorry I'm late.

04:02.360 --> 04:04.278
I got hung up
with something.

04:04.362 --> 04:05.446
What do we got?

04:05.513 --> 04:06.897
A child abduction
in St. Louis.

04:06.948 --> 04:08.883
Yeah. Bobby Smith,
9 years old,

04:08.950 --> 04:10.934
vanished 48 hours ago
from a residential area,

04:10.986 --> 04:12.369
where his mother,
Marlene Smith,

04:12.437 --> 04:13.954
claims to have
dropped him off.

04:14.039 --> 04:15.906
48 hours and we're
just learning about it now?

04:15.957 --> 04:19.076
Yeah. That's 'cause mom didn't
know her son was gone.

04:19.127 --> 04:21.411
She assumed that he was
with the grandmother

04:21.463 --> 04:23.214
and just left him there.

04:23.281 --> 04:25.216
So, she's not exactly on the short
list for mother of the year.

04:25.283 --> 04:26.783
What about the father?

04:26.835 --> 04:29.786
Uh, he was convicted of embezzling
from his workplace 2 years ago.

04:29.838 --> 04:31.889
Currently cooling his heels
in state prison.

04:31.956 --> 04:34.791
If it's a stranger abduction,
the first 24 hours are critical.

04:34.843 --> 04:36.894
This kid's already been
missing twice that long.

04:36.961 --> 04:39.530
Which is why we shouldn't
waste any more time. Let's go.

04:46.321 --> 04:47.971
I brought you something
to eat, Bobby.

04:48.023 --> 04:49.306
Gotta go to work now.

04:49.357 --> 04:51.775
When can I see my mom?

04:53.945 --> 04:56.080
I already told you.

04:56.147 --> 04:58.749
We'll talk about
your mom later.

04:58.816 --> 05:00.701
No! Don't go!

05:26.394 --> 05:30.394
